{
  "stem": "22447.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, as soon as the alarm went up-- so Churchill called an emergency meeting with the chiefs of staff and the navy and the air force, and they threw everything they had into it, the battle ships, the cruisers, whatever they had, the [INAUDIBLE]-- everything, because this was the big showdown they were waiting for.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They threw everything they had into it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Well, when the Italians saw these big battle ships coming up and the cruisers, they unhooked the barges, turned round and went for Marseilles.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So the barges were left floating in the channel because they can't move themselves.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then, an argument cropped up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The RAF said we want to finish it off, the navy said we want to finish it off.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So at the end the day, Churchill said let the RAF finish off.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of course, that's just the boost they need for the morale after the Battle of Britain.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said, that's the best thing that they can have.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the RAF made a circle of incendiary bombs around the barges and gradually they closed in.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were all bones and the dead bodies are washed up in the Isle of Wight.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's why we was stopped from going to the beaches.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And moving forward, what were the next sort of major series of events that happened in your army career?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The next series-- after that, the-- that was on a Sunday.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The following day on the Monday, Churchill sent a memo to the then chief of staff, Lord-- Lord Alan Brooke, he was chief.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He sent him a memo, prepare for the invasion to Europe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that took four years of careful planning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Normandy landings took four years of very, very careful planning, rehearsals, and nothing should go wrong.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
